			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-06-07T14:07:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2016/06/wp-mobile-detector-vulnerability-being-exploited-in-the-wild.html#comment-7697">June 7, 2016</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>hi</p>
<p>please run this command if you have shell access to your web site  root </p>
<p>this is only find out the last file modified by hackers (only at linux servers)</p>
<p>then you can remove or edit affected files with precaution.(please first the php file the try to remove it)</p>
<p>find  -type f -mtime -7</p>
<p>this command will find the files modified for last 7 days you can change or increase  this number  if you couldn&#8217;t  find the file or files.</p>
		</div>

		
		
